ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Rapid diagnosis is and has always been an important veterinary need,
whatever transboundary disease one is discussing. Speed in diagnosis
has a massive impact on the efficiency of stopping any epidemic. But
vaccination depends on the national budget and veterinary services
efficiency in the field. Too often it is invoked after things have
got out of hand. And with avian influenza it merely stops the birds
demonstrating clinical signs. They still get viraemic, though at a
lower titre. The risk of disease spread is only decreased, not
eliminated. - Mod.MHJ]
